column5: Well isn't this a perfect new culinary experience for Aziraphale ^^
It's funny, just wrong for this sub.

Thank you for writing this. I struggle with all of this, plus the feeling that "this isn't real depression" and "you aren't sick enough". And I don't know how to talk to anyone about these feelings because I feel like no one would believe me. Sure, my friends and co-workers may see me as introverted, kinda weird, kinda socially inept...but overall successful and often smiling and trying to make connections.. a person like this can't be having  a conversation with themselves everyday on the pros and cons of continuing living..
